    "en": {
      "title": "Joe Biden's Action Notice on Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "At today's G7 summit, US President Joe Biden announced an additional $ 20 million in aid to strengthen Sri Lanka's food security.",
        "The funding aims to feed 800,000 Sri Lankan children, provide nutritional support to more than 27,000 pregnant and lactating mothers, and support the school nutrition program.",
        "In addition, the initiative plans to support about 30,000 farmers to increase food production.",
        "\"President Biden's announcement of an additional $ 20 million in aid to Sri Lanka demonstrates the United States' continued commitment to food security, public health and the economic well-being of all Sri Lankans,\" said US Ambassador to Sri Lanka Julie Chung. (R)"
      ],
